  "text": "Myocardial segment shortening was analyzed in ischemic and nonischemic myocardium in four control and four PS-519-treated pigs. Subepicardial, multidirectional ultrasonic 0.7-mm dimension crystals (Sonometrics; Ontario, Canada) were implanted 10 mm apart in the minor axis plane to subtend the myocardial region supplied by the LAD and to measure longitudinal segment length shortening with highfrequency sampling (Ͼ100 Hz) [CITATION_1] . Segmental shortening in the ischemic and nonischemic regions was compared, at the indicated time points (Table 1) , using Sonosoft sonomicrometer analysis software (version 3.1.0, Sonometrics).",
